modules.description: Provides functions to create, update, and query persistent lists with efficient appending and indexing. Operates on a custom list structure optimized for immutability and performance. Used to manage large, evolving datasets in applications requiring frequent modifications without full list reconstruction.

Converts between JSON strings and binary plist representations, with support for file I/O and Yojson integration. Operates on the `plist` type, handling structured data like dictionaries and arrays. Used to read and write property list files in both text and binary formats, and to serialize/deserialize data for interop with Objective-C.
